cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the application of full duplex communication to self-backhauled small cells, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes an interference-aware scheduling method to maximize the FD gain across multiple UEs in both uplink and downlink directions, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the scheduling and power allocation in wireless communication networks, which falls under the scope of communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a scheduling and power allocation algorithm, which can be considered as a control system for the wireless network. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the throughput improvement of small cells, which can be related to multimedia applications that require high data rates.
